# PostgreSQL RLS & RPC Strictness

- REQUIRE Row Level Security (RLS) on ALL tables (`proof_ledger`, `picture`, `video`, `courier_packages`).
- REQUIRE policies to explicitly handle `INSERT`, `UPDATE`, `DELETE`, and `SELECT` using `auth.uid()`.
- FORBID direct `SELECT` on black-box tables like `courier_packages`. Access must be gated through RPCs like `attempt_courier_unlock`.
- REQUIRE `SECURITY DEFINER` only on strictly necessary RPCs, with explicitly declared `SET search_path = public`.
